summary:
In this paper we consider the following Schr\"odinger-Poisson system in the
whole $\mathbb R^{3}$, \begin{equation*}
  \left\{
  \begin{array}{ll}
  -\Delta u+u+ \lambda \phi u=f(u) &\text{ in } \mathbb R^3,
  -\Delta \phi= u^2 &\text{ in } \mathbb R^3,
  \end{array}
  \right. \end{equation*} where $\lambda>0$ and the nonlinearity $f$ is
"asymptotically cubic" at infinity. This implies that the nonlocal term $\phi
u$ and the nonlinear term $f(u)$ are, in some sense, in a strict competition.
We show that the system admits a least energy sign-changing and radial solution
obtained by minimizing the energy functional on the so-called {nodal Nehari
set).
